cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.DL, cs.SI

This paper is about analyzing user engagement with citations on Wikipedia, which involves studying user behavior and interactions with links. This falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and digital libraries (cs.DL). Additionally, the study involves analyzing the content of the citations and their relevance to the user, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and social media (cs.SI). Finally, the study also touches on the quality of Wikipedia pages, which could be classified under cybernetics (cs.CY).
